    Step 2 of the Smith-Waterman algorithm.
    Backtracks through the matrix from cells with the maximum cell score to obtain optimal alignments.
    This step is distributed.
    Returns an ArrayList of all optimal alignments and the index of their alignment locations.

        Step 2 of the Smith-Waterman algorithm.
        Backtracks through the matrix from cells with the maximum cell score to obtain optimal alignments.
        This step is distributed.
        Returns an ArrayList of all optimal alignments and the index of their alignment locations.

        Specified by:
        call in interface org.apache.spark.api.java.function.Function3<java.util.ArrayList<int[]>,scala.Tuple2<int[][],char[][]>,scala.Tuple2<java.lang.String[],char[]>,java.util.ArrayList<scala.Tuple2<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String[]>>>
        Parameters:
        cell -

          The (i,j) coordinates of the starting cell

        matrixInfo -

          A Tuple2 of other data required to extract the optimal alignments.
            A String[] of the sequences in this comparison - reference sequence , read
            char[] alignment types - alignment, insertion, deletion, none

        matrices -

          A Tuple2 of matrices filled in Step 1.
            int[][] - matrix of scores
            char[][] - matrix of corresponding alignment types.

        Returns:

          A Tuple2 of the index of the beginning of the alignment with respect to the reference sequence, and how the sequences are aligned.
